+# F7 US3 — Member quota dashboard + history + Q15 banner
+
+## Summary
+
+Ships F7 User Story 3 of the Email Broadcast (E-Blast) feature: paying-tier members can now see their annual e-blast entitlement, year-to-date used / reserved / remaining counts, the next reset date in tenant timezone, a paginated history of their own broadcasts, a per-broadcast detail page with delivery breakdown (delivered / bounced / soft-bounced / complained), and a GDPR Art. 7 acknowledgement banner. Cross-member probes return 404 + emit `broadcast_cross_member_probe` audit (anti-enumeration with observable signal).
+
+## Specification
+
+- `specs/010-email-broadcast/spec.md` — US3 AS1–AS9 + Q15 banner + Q19 per-tenant scope
+- `specs/010-email-broadcast/contracts/broadcasts-api.md` § 1.7 — `nextResetAt` + `tenantTimezone` envelope
+- Constitution v1.4.0 Principle I (tenant isolation), II (TDD), III (Clean Architecture)
+
+## Implementation
+
+**New surfaces**:
+- `/portal/benefits/e-blasts` — quota panel + history table + AS2 plan-changed explainer + Q15 banner mount
+- `/portal/broadcasts/[id]` — detail page with delivery breakdown
+- `POST /api/portal/broadcasts/acknowledge` — GDPR Art. 7 demonstrable consent
+- `GET /api/broadcasts/quota` extended with `nextResetAt` + `tenantTimezone`
+
+**Application use-cases** (`src/modules/broadcasts/application/use-cases/`):
+- `compute-quota-counter.ts` — extended with `nextResetAtFor` helper (single source of truth for AS1 microcopy + API contract field)
+- `get-member-broadcast.ts` — read path with `findOwnedByMember` discriminated union; emits `broadcast_cross_member_probe` on cross-member access; emits `broadcasts.enumeration_probe.not_found` info log on pure UUID enumeration
+- `acknowledge-broadcasts-terms.ts` — Q15 GDPR Art. 7 consent recorder with discriminated `'fresh' | 'idempotent'` output; surfaces `ack.repo_error` for F3 DB failures (no silent 200-OK with lost consent)
+- `list-member-broadcasts.ts` — port-routed paginated history reader
+
+**Infrastructure**:
+- `BroadcastsRepo.{listForMemberPaginated, findOwnedByMember, aggregateDeliveryCountsForBroadcast}` — three new RLS-bound queries
+- `MemberRepo.{findLastPlanChangedAt, updateBroadcastsAcknowledgedAtInTx}` — atomic UPDATE for race-free GDPR Art. 7 first-consent anchor preservation
+- `IanaTimezone` branded VO + `getTenantTimezone(slug)` helper (single-tenant config, F12 multi-tenant TODO documented)
+
+**Migrations**:
+- `0077_broadcasts_member_history_idx.sql` — `(tenant_id, requested_by_member_id, created_at DESC, broadcast_id DESC)` covering index for OFFSET-paginated history
+- `0078_audit_log_member_plan_changed_idx.sql` — partial index keyed on `(tenant_id, payload->>'memberId', timestamp DESC, id DESC) WHERE event_type='member_plan_changed'` to keep `findLastPlanChangedAt` index-only beyond audit_log's tens-of-millions horizon
+
+**DB tooling fix**: `drizzle.config.ts` was pointing at `public.drizzle_migrations` (drizzle-kit default) while `pnpm db:migrate` uses `drizzle.__drizzle_migrations` (postgres-js migrator default). Unified to one journal so `drizzle-kit migrate` no longer crashes on duplicate enum types from re-applying older migrations.
+
